# 1. Executive Summary

The application was vulnerable to a **Blind OS Command Injection** in the `email` parameter of the feedback form.

Although the command output was not returned in the HTTP response, it was possible to redirect the output of the injected command to a publicly accessible file within the web server's document root. Retrieving this file confirmed successful command execution on the underlying operating system.

