# 10. Impact Analysis

Successful exploitation allows an attacker to execute arbitrary operating system commands.

Depending on the privileges assigned to the web server process, this may lead to:

- System reconnaissance
- Disclosure of sensitive files
- Remote code execution
- Malware deployment
- Privilege escalation
- Complete server compromise

---

# 11. Root Cause

The application constructs operating system commands using unsanitized user input.

Specifically, it lacks:

- Input validation
- Input sanitization
- Safe escaping of shell metacharacters
- Secure APIs that avoid invoking the system shell

---

# 12. Recommendations

## High Priority

Avoid invoking operating system commands whenever possible.

## High Priority

Use language-native APIs instead of shell commands.

## High Priority

Strictly validate and sanitize all user-supplied input.

## Medium Priority

Run the application using the principle of least privilege.

## Medium Priority

Prevent public access to directories that may contain application-generated files.

## Low Priority

Implement monitoring and alerting for suspicious shell metacharacters such as:

```
|
||
&
&&
;
`
$()
>
<
```

