# 14. Conclusion

The assessment confirmed the presence of a **Blind OS Command Injection** vulnerability.

Although the application did not directly disclose command output, redirecting the output to a publicly accessible file allowed successful retrieval of the execution result.

This demonstrates that an attacker can execute arbitrary operating system commands and obtain sensitive information from the underlying host, representing a significant risk to the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of the affected system.
